Replace the hardcoded 3-value allowlist in `message-sender.ts` with a direct passthrough, and add tests verifying `dontAsk` and `auto` modes pass through correctly.

## File to modify

### `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/message-sender.ts` (lines 223-231)

Replace this code:
```typescript
sdkOptions.permissionMode =
  session.permissionMode === 'bypassPermissions' ||
  session.permissionMode === 'plan' ||
  session.permissionMode === 'acceptEdits'
    ? session.permissionMode
    : 'default';
if (session.permissionMode === 'bypassPermissions') {
  sdkOptions.allowDangerouslySkipPermissions = true;
}
```

With:
```typescript
// Pass the session's permission mode directly to the SDK.
// The schema validates valid values upstream; no allowlist needed here.
sdkOptions.permissionMode = session.permissionMode;
if (session.permissionMode === 'bypassPermissions') {
  sdkOptions.allowDangerouslySkipPermissions = true;
}
```

This is the critical fix. The old code silently converted any unrecognized mode to `default`, including `dontAsk` and `auto`. Since `PermissionModeSchema` validates all values at the API boundary (route handlers), there's no need for a redundant allowlist in the message sender.

## Tests to add

Add tests in `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/__tests__/claude-code-runtime.test.ts` (or whichever test file exercises `sendMessage` SDK options). Follow the existing test patterns in that file.

```typescript
it('passes dontAsk mode directly to SDK query options', async () => {
  // Set up session with permissionMode: 'dontAsk'
  agentManager.ensureSession('s1', { permissionMode: 'dontAsk' });
  // Mock the SDK query to capture options
  // Send a message and verify sdkOptions.permissionMode === 'dontAsk'
  // Verify allowDangerouslySkipPermissions is NOT set
});

it('passes auto mode directly to SDK query options', async () => {
  // Set up session with permissionMode: 'auto'
  agentManager.ensureSession('s1', { permissionMode: 'auto' });
  // Mock the SDK query to capture options
  // Send a message and verify sdkOptions.permissionMode === 'auto'
  // Verify allowDangerouslySkipPermissions is NOT set
});

it('preserves allowDangerouslySkipPermissions for bypassPermissions', async () => {
  agentManager.ensureSession('s1', { permissionMode: 'bypassPermissions' });
  // Send a message and verify sdkOptions.permissionMode === 'bypassPermissions'
  // Verify allowDangerouslySkipPermissions === true
});

it('passes default mode directly without transformation', async () => {
  agentManager.ensureSession('s1', { permissionMode: 'default' });
  // Send a message and verify sdkOptions.permissionMode === 'default'
  // Verify allowDangerouslySkipPermissions is NOT set
});
```

These tests verify the old silent-fallback behavior is gone: previously `dontAsk` and `auto` would silently become `default`. Now they pass through directly.

## Acceptance criteria

- `sdkOptions.permissionMode` always equals `session.permissionMode` (no transformation)
- `allowDangerouslySkipPermissions` is only set for `bypassPermissions`
- All 4 new tests pass
- Existing permission-mode-related tests continue to pass
- `pnpm typecheck` passes

Convert `updateSession()` from synchronous to async across the AgentRuntime interface, session store, and runtime implementations. When `setPermissionMode()` fails on an active SDK query, revert the in-memory permission mode and throw the error so the route handler can return 422.

## Files to modify

### 1. `packages/shared/src/agent-runtime.ts` (line 153)

Change the `updateSession` return type from `boolean` to `boolean | Promise<boolean>`:
```typescript
/** Update mutable session fields. Returns false if the session does not exist. */
updateSession(
  sessionId: string,
  opts: {
    permissionMode?: PermissionMode;
    model?: string;
    effort?: EffortLevel;
    fastMode?: boolean;
    autoMode?: boolean;
  }
): boolean | Promise<boolean>;
```

The union `boolean | Promise<boolean>` allows synchronous implementations (TestModeRuntime, FakeAgentRuntime) to continue returning `boolean` without wrapping in `Promise.resolve()`.

### 2. `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/session-store.ts` (lines 164-194)

Change `updateSession()` to be async and await `setPermissionMode()` with error handling and revert:
```typescript
async updateSession(
  sessionId: string,
  opts: {
    permissionMode?: PermissionMode;
    model?: string;
    effort?: EffortLevel;
    fastMode?: boolean;
    autoMode?: boolean;
  }
): Promise<boolean> {
  let session = this.findSession(sessionId);
  if (!session) {
    this.ensureSession(sessionId, {
      permissionMode: opts.permissionMode ?? 'default',
      hasStarted: false,
    });
    this.sessions.get(sessionId)!.needsTranscriptCheck = true;
    session = this.sessions.get(sessionId)!;
  }
  if (opts.permissionMode) {
    const prevMode = session.permissionMode;
    logger.debug('[updateSession] permissionMode change', {
      sessionId,
      from: prevMode,
      to: opts.permissionMode,
    });
    session.permissionMode = opts.permissionMode;
    if (session.activeQuery) {
      try {
        await session.activeQuery.setPermissionMode(opts.permissionMode);
      } catch (err) {
        // Revert in-memory state on SDK rejection
        session.permissionMode = prevMode;
        logger.error('[updateSession] setPermissionMode failed', { sessionId, err });
        throw err;
      }
    }
  }
  if (opts.model) session.model = opts.model;
  if (opts.effort) session.effort = opts.effort;
  if (opts.fastMode !== undefined) session.fastMode = opts.fastMode;
  if (opts.autoMode !== undefined) session.autoMode = opts.autoMode;
  return true;
}
```

### 3. `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/claude-code-runtime.ts` (around line 184)

Update the `updateSession()` method to be async and await the session store:
```typescript
async updateSession(
  sessionId: string,
  opts: {
    permissionMode?: PermissionMode;
    model?: string;
    effort?: EffortLevel;
    fastMode?: boolean;
    autoMode?: boolean;
  }
): Promise<boolean> {
  return this.sessionStore.updateSession(sessionId, opts);
}
```

### 4. `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/test-mode/test-mode-runtime.ts` (line 52-66)

No changes needed. The `updateSession()` method already returns `boolean` which satisfies the `boolean | Promise<boolean>` union type.

### 5. `packages/test-utils/src/fake-agent-runtime.ts` (line 71-82)

No changes needed. The `vi.fn()` mock already returns `boolean` which satisfies the union type.

